Ok, I'm somewhat new to the game, been playing since maybe august or so.<br>
<br>
Played around with a bunch of different characters, but dont have a ton of time to play.  I generally play with my girlfriend.<br>
<br>
So, the deal is, I have tried most classes, and have characters in the 10-17 range in warrior, enchanter, magician, bard, and ranger classes.  Other classes are lower levels so far.  But I am enjoying playing my warrior grouped with her shaman quite a bit.  I also enjoy my enchanter, but that will be a post on a different class board <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I just have a lot of questions about basic stuff that isnt really out there easy to find.  <br>
<br>
I am an ogre warrior, level 11 so far.  I want to be able to get some levels quickly, to get to see more of the game.  Assuming that I have a shaman working with me, with decent gear herself, what sort of things should I look at as far as questing, good places to get exp, good equipment to use?<br>
<br>
First, I want to figure out how I should be working with my gear.  I manage to make reasonable money, and have around 1000 pp to play with, and could get more within a reasonable timeframe.  I currently have a centi shortsword and blackened alloy bastard sword that I bought, and have been using those two weapons skills exclusivly.  My armor varies from complete crap (ie, tattered leather) to decent (my bp is AC 17).  I dont know what to look for on a decent budget.  My plan before coming here was to keep saving for a FBSS, since haste seems so powerfull.  The other thing I was thinking of working towards is the Iksar breastplate for the regen.  Should I aim for these goals, or just worry about getting the AC up as high as I can?<br>
<br>
Second is hunting.  So far I really dont know where to hunt.  As an Ogre my options are limited.  I'm only dubious in Halas, and the PoK lets me do selling and banking ok.   But so far hunting in halas has been mediocre, blackburrow is starting to find dark blues at this point, never mind yellows.  Outdoor hunting in Halas is starting to feel the same.  I tried going to EC and taking an orc camp (partly to help faction), and the exp sucked.  I was thinking of the Dervish camps in WC, but I only went there once with a friend, I dont know if they are the right level range.  So, whats a good place to get exp in the 12-20 range?  <br>
<br>
Finally I am curious how guilds work.  My GF was asked if she wanted to join a guild, so we did, but they seem somewhat inactive, and what players there are are much higher level.  I dont see a whole lot of use in being in this guild at this point, but the more I read about applications etc, I dont want to just bail and hope I get into a guild later.  What sort of guild options are there where I could reasonably expect to round up a group to hunt with at my level range, or is that asking too much for a guild?  Should I be guildless until I get to the level where people start needing bigger groups?  Or should I stick out with this guild and hope more people come on around my level range?<br>
<br>
I know its a lot of questions, but I really do absorb things quite well, and I think I can do ok even without help, I just really want to maximize my time online.  with only 3-4 hours a night, 3-4 nights a week, I want to try and see the higher end of the game before next winter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have lots of time to browse websites and dig thru alakazams website during the day, but I try not to play and get too far ahead of my gf during this time.<br>
<br>
-Gorbage<br>
